00:09:55.460 --> 00:09:59.000 align:middle line:84%
One of the problems that we
have in the world right now

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:00.600 align:middle line:90%
is empathy.

00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:01.400 align:middle line:90%
What, Dave?

00:10:01.400 --> 00:10:03.080 align:middle line:84%
Did you just say that
empathy is a problem?

00:10:03.080 --> 00:10:03.880 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:10:03.880 --> 00:10:07.820 align:middle line:84%
Empathy is the first step on
building a spiritual practice,

00:10:07.820 --> 00:10:11.070 align:middle line:84%
because the ability to feel
another person's emotions,

00:10:11.070 --> 00:10:12.990 align:middle line:84%
whether they're
positive or negative,

00:10:12.990 --> 00:10:15.043 align:middle line:84%
that's very, very
important for you.

00:10:15.043 --> 00:10:16.460 align:middle line:84%
And if you can't
feel that, you're

00:10:16.460 --> 00:10:18.140 align:middle line:84%
not going to be a
very nice person.

00:10:18.140 --> 00:10:22.890 align:middle line:84%
But once you feel empathy, if
you feel everyone's pain all

00:10:22.890 --> 00:10:25.840 align:middle line:84%
the time, you will be
disabled by your empathy.

00:10:25.840 --> 00:10:27.970 align:middle line:84%
And this is a major
problem today.

00:10:27.970 --> 00:10:31.022 align:middle line:84%
So what you do when you
create automatic kindness,

00:10:31.022 --> 00:10:32.730 align:middle line:84%
and I'm about to tell
you how to do that,

00:10:32.730 --> 00:10:35.940 align:middle line:84%
is you learn to
wish well for others

00:10:35.940 --> 00:10:38.460 align:middle line:84%
without having to
take on their pain.

00:10:38.460 --> 00:10:40.020 align:middle line:90%
And that is called compassion.

00:10:40.020 --> 00:10:43.260 align:middle line:84%
And compassion is a
higher spiritual state

00:10:43.260 --> 00:10:44.610 align:middle line:90%
than just empathy.

00:10:44.610 --> 00:10:45.600 align:middle line:90%
So they're both good.

00:10:45.600 --> 00:10:47.255 align:middle line:90%
But compassion is a lot better.

00:10:47.255 --> 00:10:48.630 align:middle line:84%
So you can see
someone suffering.

00:10:48.630 --> 00:10:51.250 align:middle line:84%
You can decide to help them
if it's within your means.

00:10:51.250 --> 00:10:54.150 align:middle line:84%
But if it's not
yours to handle, you

00:10:54.150 --> 00:10:56.400 align:middle line:84%
don't have to suffer for the
rest of the day on behalf

00:10:56.400 --> 00:10:57.270 align:middle line:90%
of someone else.

00:10:57.270 --> 00:10:59.550 align:middle line:84%
Now I've just
mentioned forgiveness.

00:10:59.550 --> 00:11:01.410 align:middle line:84%
A lot of us, including
me, have been

00:11:01.410 --> 00:11:03.990 align:middle line:90%
through substantial traumas.

00:11:03.990 --> 00:11:07.860 align:middle line:10%
Forgiveness is a specific
neurological, spiritual state

00:11:07.860 --> 00:11:11.550 align:middle line:10%
that I've taught 1,500
entrepreneurs and actors

00:11:11.550 --> 00:11:15.750 align:middle line:10%
and pro-athletes how to do using
neurofeedback and neuroscience.

00:11:15.750 --> 00:11:18.810 align:middle line:84%
Forgiveness is not saying that
something that happened to you

00:11:18.810 --> 00:11:19.650 align:middle line:90%
is OK.

00:11:19.650 --> 00:11:26.130 align:middle line:10%
It is not saying that something
bad that happened was OK

00:11:26.130 --> 00:11:30.570 align:middle line:10%
or telling the person who did
it to you that you forgive them.

00:11:30.570 --> 00:11:34.560 align:middle line:84%
Forgiveness is about you
turning off an automatic fear

00:11:34.560 --> 00:11:36.540 align:middle line:84%
and anxiety response
to something.

00:11:36.540 --> 00:11:40.270 align:middle line:10%
It means letting go of a
grudge so that it no longer can

00:11:40.270 --> 00:11:41.070 align:middle line:10%
trigger you.

00:11:41.070 --> 00:11:43.050 align:middle line:10%
So you can be non-reactive.

00:11:43.050 --> 00:11:46.800 align:middle line:10%
When you forgive, which is part
of the reset process that's

00:11:46.800 --> 00:11:48.660 align:middle line:10%
in my books and in
my content online

00:11:48.660 --> 00:11:51.750 align:middle line:10%
at my neuroscience company,
it's a structured process.

00:11:51.750 --> 00:11:55.830 align:middle line:84%
And it permanently removes
automated unkindness.

00:11:55.830 --> 00:11:59.130 align:middle line:84%
And you can see this in
people's brainwave patterns.

00:11:59.130 --> 00:12:02.580 align:middle line:84%
Think about it like this you're
driving in traffic and someone

00:12:02.580 --> 00:12:03.630 align:middle line:90%
cuts you off.

00:12:03.630 --> 00:12:06.120 align:middle line:84%
Now the normal
response that I've

00:12:06.120 --> 00:12:08.640 align:middle line:84%
had for the first
half of my life

00:12:08.640 --> 00:12:12.192 align:middle line:84%
involved having very built up
muscles around my middle finger

00:12:12.192 --> 00:12:14.400 align:middle line:84%
because I probably would
have flipped the person off,

00:12:14.400 --> 00:12:15.480 align:middle line:90%
I would have got mad.

00:12:15.480 --> 00:12:18.240 align:middle line:84%
And my body would have
automatically created

00:12:18.240 --> 00:12:20.098 align:middle line:84%
a story that this
person cut me off

00:12:20.098 --> 00:12:22.140 align:middle line:84%
because they think they're
more important than me

00:12:22.140 --> 00:12:25.230 align:middle line:84%
and it doesn't matter
and how unjust it is

00:12:25.230 --> 00:12:26.970 align:middle line:90%
and all sorts of whatever.

00:12:26.970 --> 00:12:29.640 align:middle line:84%
Now that's not a
very healthy response

00:12:29.640 --> 00:12:31.900 align:middle line:90%
because it didn't make me happy.

00:12:31.900 --> 00:12:33.120 align:middle line:90%
It made me unhappy.

00:12:33.120 --> 00:12:35.920 align:middle line:84%
And it didn't change the fact
the person was in front of me.

00:12:35.920 --> 00:12:40.530 align:middle line:84%
So an equally valid
story is that the person

00:12:40.530 --> 00:12:43.560 align:middle line:84%
is on the way to the hospital
for the birth of their child

00:12:43.560 --> 00:12:45.540 align:middle line:84%
or to see their mom
before she passes away.

00:12:45.540 --> 00:12:46.620 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter.

00:12:46.620 --> 00:12:50.100 align:middle line:84%
What's going on here is I get
to choose my state because I'm

00:12:50.100 --> 00:12:52.860 align:middle line:84%
no longer triggered by someone
cutting me off because I

00:12:52.860 --> 00:12:54.750 align:middle line:90%
changed the story around it.

00:12:54.750 --> 00:12:59.130 align:middle line:84%
And the way you activate
this forgiveness and the way

00:12:59.130 --> 00:13:03.120 align:middle line:84%
you do what I call a spiritual
reset is you actually seek out

00:13:03.120 --> 00:13:04.260 align:middle line:90%
a triggering memory.

00:13:04.260 --> 00:13:08.460 align:middle line:84%
What's the first time you felt
the way that you feel when you

00:13:08.460 --> 00:13:10.050 align:middle line:84%
get triggered by
something, something

00:13:10.050 --> 00:13:12.000 align:middle line:84%
you just really have
a hard time handling.

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:15.270 align:middle line:84%
And if you just sit with
that and you feel into it,

00:13:15.270 --> 00:13:17.520 align:middle line:84%
you're going to see a
picture in your head.

00:13:17.520 --> 00:13:19.020 align:middle line:90%
Something's going to appear.

00:13:19.020 --> 00:13:20.730 align:middle line:84%
It's usually something
from childhood

00:13:20.730 --> 00:13:23.120 align:middle line:84%
that doesn't make
any sense sometimes.

00:13:23.120 --> 00:13:26.000 align:middle line:84%
And as you do that, you'll say,
Oh, that is the first time.

00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:28.320 align:middle line:84%
I forgot about
that all the time.

00:13:28.320 --> 00:13:29.570 align:middle line:90%
So I'm like, Oh, that's weird.

00:13:29.570 --> 00:13:32.150 align:middle line:84%
My nervous system as a
40 something year old

00:13:32.150 --> 00:13:34.970 align:middle line:84%
is still running
programming from first grade

00:13:34.970 --> 00:13:36.560 align:middle line:90%
that I had forgotten all about.

00:13:36.560 --> 00:13:38.060 align:middle line:90%
None of this is conscious.

00:13:38.060 --> 00:13:39.950 align:middle line:84%
This is all in your
operating system.

00:13:39.950 --> 00:13:42.950 align:middle line:84%
And a spiritual practice
around forgiveness

00:13:42.950 --> 00:13:45.380 align:middle line:84%
allows you to go in
and find those states.

00:13:45.380 --> 00:13:50.090 align:middle line:84%
And you actually re-experience
the pain as best you can.

00:13:50.090 --> 00:13:54.800 align:middle line:84%
What I want you to be able
to do is then literally sit

00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:56.120 align:middle line:90%
the person across from you.

00:13:56.120 --> 00:13:58.940 align:middle line:84%
You visualize them across from
you with your eyes closed.

00:13:58.940 --> 00:14:02.180 align:middle line:84%
And you see it from
their perspective.

00:14:02.180 --> 00:14:05.970 align:middle line:84%
And you ask yourself, what
did that person's parents

00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:06.770 align:middle line:90%
do to them?

00:14:06.770 --> 00:14:08.210 align:middle line:84%
What had to happen
to that person

00:14:08.210 --> 00:14:10.130 align:middle line:84%
to make them do whatever
it was they did?

00:14:10.130 --> 00:14:12.210 align:middle line:90%
Like how bad is their life?

00:14:12.210 --> 00:14:15.470 align:middle line:84%
Can you see it from
their point of view?

00:14:15.470 --> 00:14:17.540 align:middle line:84%
And the reality is
that if you look

00:14:17.540 --> 00:14:19.760 align:middle line:84%
at it from their point
of view, they probably

00:14:19.760 --> 00:14:21.910 align:middle line:84%
didn't even what they
were doing or maybe they

00:14:21.910 --> 00:14:23.560 align:middle line:84%
knew what they
were doing but they

00:14:23.560 --> 00:14:26.410 align:middle line:84%
did that because their
operating system was programmed

00:14:26.410 --> 00:14:29.690 align:middle line:84%
by all kinds of abuse and
other things like that.

00:14:29.690 --> 00:14:33.040 align:middle line:84%
So what you realize is that
it wasn't about you at all.

00:14:33.040 --> 00:14:36.310 align:middle line:84%
And you can actually
forgive the other person

00:14:36.310 --> 00:14:37.990 align:middle line:84%
once you see it from
their perspective.

00:14:37.990 --> 00:14:40.720 align:middle line:84%
But the trick is
you felt the pain,

00:14:40.720 --> 00:14:42.790 align:middle line:84%
you allowed yourself,
Oh, God that really hurt.

00:14:42.790 --> 00:14:44.830 align:middle line:84%
You've seen it from
their point of view.

00:14:44.830 --> 00:14:46.540 align:middle line:84%
And then you
actually do your best

00:14:46.540 --> 00:14:49.060 align:middle line:84%
to generate a sense of
feeling of forgiveness

00:14:49.060 --> 00:14:51.770 align:middle line:84%
that actually comes from your
heart to the other person.

00:14:51.770 --> 00:14:54.340 align:middle line:10%
And when you're feeling
that acceptance,

00:14:54.340 --> 00:14:58.120 align:middle line:10%
you want to turn on the most
blissful state you can imagine.

00:14:58.120 --> 00:15:01.390 align:middle line:10%
And this is a state where you
feel your heart physically

00:15:01.390 --> 00:15:04.690 align:middle line:10%
open, your eyes are
closed, your attention

00:15:04.690 --> 00:15:06.910 align:middle line:10%
is on your third
eye, which puts you

00:15:06.910 --> 00:15:10.390 align:middle line:10%
into a specific brain state
that makes it easier to forgive.

00:15:10.390 --> 00:15:14.830 align:middle line:84%
And you sit there and
then you bring a feeling

00:15:14.830 --> 00:15:17.532 align:middle line:84%
in the hairs on your body,
in your thighs, in your hips,

00:15:17.532 --> 00:15:19.990 align:middle line:84%
in your heart, in your neck,
in your arms, your whole body.

00:15:19.990 --> 00:15:21.470 align:middle line:90%
A feeling of glowing.

00:15:21.470 --> 00:15:23.060 align:middle line:90%
A feeling of happiness.

00:15:23.060 --> 00:15:24.560 align:middle line:90%
A feeling of gratitude.

00:15:24.560 --> 00:15:27.080 align:middle line:84%
And when your body
feels the painful state

00:15:27.080 --> 00:15:28.910 align:middle line:84%
and the blissful
state, it realizes

00:15:28.910 --> 00:15:30.350 align:middle line:90%
that it was making a mistake.

00:15:30.350 --> 00:15:32.510 align:middle line:90%
And it brings the two together.

00:15:32.510 --> 00:15:33.710 align:middle line:90%
But here's the magic.

00:15:33.710 --> 00:15:36.740 align:middle line:84%
During this process, you
have to find something

00:15:36.740 --> 00:15:38.130 align:middle line:90%
that you're grateful for.

00:15:38.130 --> 00:15:40.850 align:middle line:84%
And I have worked through this
with people who are actually

00:15:40.850 --> 00:15:43.350 align:middle line:84%
tortured when they come to
my neuroscience clinic in war

00:15:43.350 --> 00:15:44.150 align:middle line:90%
situations.

00:15:44.150 --> 00:15:46.070 align:middle line:84%
I've worked with
combat veterans.

00:15:46.070 --> 00:15:48.590 align:middle line:84%
I've worked with people
who had incredible losses

00:15:48.590 --> 00:15:49.400 align:middle line:90%
in their lives.

00:15:49.400 --> 00:15:52.407 align:middle line:84%
And the hardest thing is to sit
there and say you just talked

00:15:52.407 --> 00:15:53.990 align:middle line:84%
about all the bad
stuff that happened.

00:15:53.990 --> 00:15:56.360 align:middle line:84%
Name one good thing
that came out of that.

00:15:56.360 --> 00:15:58.130 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have
to be a big thing.

00:15:58.130 --> 00:16:01.170 align:middle line:84%
It can be I'm thankful
I still have my legs.

00:16:01.170 --> 00:16:01.970 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:16:01.970 --> 00:16:05.420 align:middle line:84%
One good thing, because the way
your operating system is set up

00:16:05.420 --> 00:16:09.890 align:middle line:84%
is you cannot forgive anyone or
anything until you experience

00:16:09.890 --> 00:16:11.250 align:middle line:90%
gratitude.

00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:14.540 align:middle line:84%
Gratitude is the thing that
allows you to do forgiveness.

00:16:14.540 --> 00:16:18.932 align:middle line:10%
So you sit there, you feel the
pain, you look for gratitude.

00:16:18.932 --> 00:16:21.140 align:middle line:10%
You look at it from the
other person's point of view.

00:16:21.140 --> 00:16:23.990 align:middle line:10%
And then you consciously turn
on the best feeling you've ever

00:16:23.990 --> 00:16:25.430 align:middle line:10%
had, the feeling of bliss.

00:16:25.430 --> 00:16:27.890 align:middle line:10%
And the bliss will
cancel that out.

00:16:27.890 --> 00:16:30.620 align:middle line:10%
I like to do this with
neurofeedback because I can

00:16:30.620 --> 00:16:31.820 align:middle line:10%
guide you into those states.

00:16:31.820 --> 00:16:34.250 align:middle line:84%
But what you're learning here
is a shortcut to something

00:16:34.250 --> 00:16:36.860 align:middle line:84%
that would be called
loving kindness meditation.

00:16:36.860 --> 00:16:39.440 align:middle line:84%
And it's something that
allows you to selectively go

00:16:39.440 --> 00:16:44.180 align:middle line:84%
through and edit out the things
that are your biggest triggers,

00:16:44.180 --> 00:16:45.800 align:middle line:84%
so that someone
can say something

00:16:45.800 --> 00:16:48.530 align:middle line:84%
to you that would normally make
you just clench up and maybe

00:16:48.530 --> 00:16:50.720 align:middle line:84%
yell at them and act
like a crazy person

00:16:50.720 --> 00:16:52.370 align:middle line:90%
and you regret it later.

00:16:52.370 --> 00:16:53.630 align:middle line:90%
You can turn all that off.

00:16:53.630 --> 00:16:55.880 align:middle line:84%
So the next time they do it,
you can just look at them

00:16:55.880 --> 00:16:57.770 align:middle line:90%
and just look at them.

00:16:57.770 --> 00:16:59.328 align:middle line:84%
And there's not a
negative feeling.

00:16:59.328 --> 00:17:00.620 align:middle line:90%
There's not a positive feeling.

00:17:00.620 --> 00:17:02.090 align:middle line:90%
There's just no charge at all.

00:17:02.090 --> 00:17:04.310 align:middle line:84%
I've spent six months of
my life with electrodes

00:17:04.310 --> 00:17:06.530 align:middle line:84%
glued to my head learning
how to do this practice

00:17:06.530 --> 00:17:09.170 align:middle line:84%
and doing it over and over
on every single trigger

00:17:09.170 --> 00:17:10.710 align:middle line:90%
I can find in my life.

00:17:10.710 --> 00:17:13.880 align:middle line:84%
And if you meet me and you
can find a way to trigger me,

00:17:13.880 --> 00:17:16.473 align:middle line:84%
I will thank you from
the bottom of my heart.

00:17:16.473 --> 00:17:18.140 align:middle line:84%
The reason for that
is that I will go in

00:17:18.140 --> 00:17:20.432 align:middle line:84%
and I will do this reset
process that I just taught you

00:17:20.432 --> 00:17:21.997 align:middle line:84%
and then it won't
bother me anymore.

00:17:21.997 --> 00:17:24.500 align:middle line:10%
So you can live
your life that way,

00:17:24.500 --> 00:17:27.089 align:middle line:10%
where every time
something happens,

00:17:27.089 --> 00:17:29.270 align:middle line:10%
you have automatic kindness.

00:17:29.270 --> 00:17:31.220 align:middle line:84%
You wish well for
others no matter

00:17:31.220 --> 00:17:34.580 align:middle line:84%
what they do to you because
you can teach your mitochondria

00:17:34.580 --> 00:17:35.390 align:middle line:90%
to do that.

00:17:35.390 --> 00:17:38.810 align:middle line:84%
Before your mitochondria
has a chance

00:17:38.810 --> 00:17:41.390 align:middle line:84%
to automatically think negative
things and look for threats

00:17:41.390 --> 00:17:42.570 align:middle line:90%
and look for bad things.

00:17:42.570 --> 00:17:45.260 align:middle line:84%
If you look for threats and
bad things, you will find them.

00:17:45.260 --> 00:17:47.870 align:middle line:84%
If you look for good
things, you will find them.

00:17:47.870 --> 00:17:49.370 align:middle line:84%
But you don't get
to do the looking.

00:17:49.370 --> 00:17:52.580 align:middle line:84%
You get to configure the
system that does the looking.

00:17:52.580 --> 00:17:54.410 align:middle line:84%
And that's why you
practice gratitude.

00:17:54.410 --> 00:17:56.030 align:middle line:84%
That's why you
practice forgiveness.

00:17:56.030 --> 00:17:58.850 align:middle line:84%
This works whether you
have a religious practice,

00:17:58.850 --> 00:18:01.640 align:middle line:84%
whether you have a
spiritual practice

00:18:01.640 --> 00:18:03.830 align:middle line:90%
from any lineage on the planet.

00:18:03.830 --> 00:18:05.330 align:middle line:10%
You can practice forgiveness.

00:18:05.330 --> 00:18:08.570 align:middle line:84%
I have done this with
advanced monks, with gurus,

00:18:08.570 --> 00:18:10.370 align:middle line:84%
and I've done it with
football players.

00:18:10.370 --> 00:18:12.050 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter.

00:18:12.050 --> 00:18:14.480 align:middle line:84%
This forgiveness state
is part of being human.

00:18:14.480 --> 00:18:16.563 align:middle line:84%
And it's the way you
program your networks

00:18:16.563 --> 00:18:17.855 align:middle line:90%
to do what you want them to do.

00:18:17.855 --> 00:18:22.810 align:middle line:90%


00:18:22.810 --> 00:18:24.850 align:middle line:84%
Now that you understand
this process,

00:18:24.850 --> 00:18:27.910 align:middle line:84%
I want you to understand
there are spiritual hacks.

00:18:27.910 --> 00:18:30.920 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to do a spiritual
practice all by yourself.

00:18:30.920 --> 00:18:32.950 align:middle line:84%
In fact, it's much harder
to do it by yourself.

00:18:32.950 --> 00:18:36.730 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that has
worked for thousands of years

00:18:36.730 --> 00:18:37.660 align:middle line:90%
is you find a guru.

00:18:37.660 --> 00:18:40.090 align:middle line:84%
In fact, there's lots
of them here on Gaia.

00:18:40.090 --> 00:18:44.380 align:middle line:84%
And latching yourself to a
single guru has some benefits.

00:18:44.380 --> 00:18:48.310 align:middle line:84%
It also has some risks because,
well, gurus tend to die.

00:18:48.310 --> 00:18:49.900 align:middle line:84%
And if you can't
get into a state

00:18:49.900 --> 00:18:52.240 align:middle line:84%
without your guru,
when your guru dies,

00:18:52.240 --> 00:18:53.970 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
a spiritual crisis.

00:18:53.970 --> 00:18:55.220 align:middle line:90%
And you don't want to do that.

00:18:55.220 --> 00:18:57.340 align:middle line:90%
So learn from a guru.

00:18:57.340 --> 00:18:59.920 align:middle line:84%
But I believe that
there's benefits

00:18:59.920 --> 00:19:02.560 align:middle line:84%
