You can edit the
invisible patterns

00:23:36.030 --> 00:23:37.830 align:middle line:84%
that you use to
interact with the world.

00:23:37.830 --> 00:23:39.370 align:middle line:90%
And I mentioned gratitude.

00:23:39.370 --> 00:23:41.340 align:middle line:84%
Gratitude is a part
of doing forgiveness.

00:23:41.340 --> 00:23:46.260 align:middle line:84%
But gratitude itself is
a way to turn off fear.

00:23:46.260 --> 00:23:48.700 align:middle line:84%
Now I'm going to tell
you a little story.

00:23:48.700 --> 00:23:51.790 align:middle line:84%
When I did my first personal
development event many,

00:23:51.790 --> 00:23:55.380 align:middle line:84%
many years ago, I was
feeling really uncomfortable.

00:23:55.380 --> 00:23:57.040 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't know why.

00:23:57.040 --> 00:24:00.090 align:middle line:84%
And the very, very
wise woman who

00:24:00.090 --> 00:24:02.520 align:middle line:84%
was running this event
she said, well, you're

00:24:02.520 --> 00:24:03.670 align:middle line:90%
not feeling your feelings.

00:24:03.670 --> 00:24:05.500 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I'm
feeling my feelings.

00:24:05.500 --> 00:24:06.300 align:middle line:90%
I'm angry.

00:24:06.300 --> 00:24:07.357 align:middle line:90%
This is really stupid.

00:24:07.357 --> 00:24:09.690 align:middle line:84%
I don't know why I signed up
for this dumb event anyway.

00:24:09.690 --> 00:24:10.490 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I said that.

00:24:10.490 --> 00:24:11.400 align:middle line:90%
I was a jerk.

00:24:11.400 --> 00:24:13.990 align:middle line:84%
And she looked at me
and she said, well,

00:24:13.990 --> 00:24:15.550 align:middle line:84%
do you feel anything
in your body?

00:24:15.550 --> 00:24:16.530 align:middle line:90%
And I said Yes.

00:24:16.530 --> 00:24:17.880 align:middle line:90%
I feel something in my stomach.

00:24:17.880 --> 00:24:19.770 align:middle line:84%
And she said, there's
a name for that.

00:24:19.770 --> 00:24:21.160 align:middle line:90%
And I said, what is it?

00:24:21.160 --> 00:24:23.100 align:middle line:90%
And she said, it's fear.

00:24:23.100 --> 00:24:26.070 align:middle line:84%
And I looked her right in
the eyes and I said Barbara,

00:24:26.070 --> 00:24:28.110 align:middle line:84%
there's no reason
for me to be afraid,

00:24:28.110 --> 00:24:29.740 align:middle line:90%
therefore I'm not afraid.

00:24:29.740 --> 00:24:34.140 align:middle line:84%
And she laughed and she
said, fear is an emotion,

00:24:34.140 --> 00:24:36.360 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't have to be rational.

00:24:36.360 --> 00:24:38.910 align:middle line:84%
And those are really
important words for you,

00:24:38.910 --> 00:24:42.540 align:middle line:84%
because if you think you're
a rational being, it's wrong.

00:24:42.540 --> 00:24:45.270 align:middle line:84%
You are an emotional
and a rational being

00:24:45.270 --> 00:24:46.470 align:middle line:90%
at the same time.

00:24:46.470 --> 00:24:49.860 align:middle line:84%
And your body has the ability
to change what you see

00:24:49.860 --> 00:24:51.870 align:middle line:84%
and to change the emotional
tune of what you see

00:24:51.870 --> 00:24:54.780 align:middle line:84%
and then you act rationally
based on bad information

00:24:54.780 --> 00:24:56.710 align:middle line:90%
from your operating system.

00:24:56.710 --> 00:25:01.500 align:middle line:84%
But if you turn on gratitude,
it takes your body out

00:25:01.500 --> 00:25:03.690 align:middle line:84%
of fight or flight mode,
out of find problems

00:25:03.690 --> 00:25:04.810 align:middle line:90%
in the world mode.

00:25:04.810 --> 00:25:08.460 align:middle line:10%
And it turns off fear even if
you don't think you have fear.

00:25:08.460 --> 00:25:09.450 align:middle line:10%
Fear can be hidden.

00:25:09.450 --> 00:25:12.990 align:middle line:84%
So a practice of
gratitude makes your life

00:25:12.990 --> 00:25:14.770 align:middle line:90%
feel like it takes less work.

00:25:14.770 --> 00:25:17.370 align:middle line:84%
So in the morning, you can
write down three things

00:25:17.370 --> 00:25:18.520 align:middle line:90%
you're grateful for.

00:25:18.520 --> 00:25:21.540 align:middle line:84%
And that will prime your brain
to look for more good things

00:25:21.540 --> 00:25:22.530 align:middle line:90%
throughout the day.

00:25:22.530 --> 00:25:25.110 align:middle line:84%
At night, you can write
down three good things

00:25:25.110 --> 00:25:27.430 align:middle line:90%
that happened to you that day.

00:25:27.430 --> 00:25:29.550 align:middle line:84%
And you'll go to
sleep without fear.

00:25:29.550 --> 00:25:31.650 align:middle line:90%
You'll go to bed more easily.

00:25:31.650 --> 00:25:33.390 align:middle line:90%
You can do a gratitude walk.

00:25:33.390 --> 00:25:36.360 align:middle line:84%
You go for a walk and just pay
close attention to everything

00:25:36.360 --> 00:25:38.910 align:middle line:84%
you see and you can be
grateful for the flower.

00:25:38.910 --> 00:25:40.680 align:middle line:84%
You can be grateful
for the clouds.

00:25:40.680 --> 00:25:41.860 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't even matter.

00:25:41.860 --> 00:25:43.830 align:middle line:84%
You just need to
turn on gratitude

00:25:43.830 --> 00:25:47.460 align:middle line:84%
and it's something you can
practice like a muscle.

00:25:47.460 --> 00:25:51.810 align:middle line:10%
And interestingly, U.J. Ramdas
who's a behavioral change

00:25:51.810 --> 00:25:55.230 align:middle line:10%
specialist figured out that you
need to experience gratitude

00:25:55.230 --> 00:25:59.670 align:middle line:10%
in your mind cognitively
and physiologically

00:25:59.670 --> 00:26:00.792 align:middle line:10%
for it to be effective.

00:26:00.792 --> 00:26:03.000 align:middle line:84%
In other words, you can't
think about being grateful.

00:26:03.000 --> 00:26:06.960 align:middle line:84%
You have to feel grateful
and think grateful.

00:26:06.960 --> 00:26:10.590 align:middle line:84%
And you can learn to turn on any
feeling in your body you want.

00:26:10.590 --> 00:26:13.620 align:middle line:84%
Turning on gratitude
is the most valuable

00:26:13.620 --> 00:26:16.330 align:middle line:84%
because you need it to
turn on forgiveness,

00:26:16.330 --> 00:26:18.090 align:middle line:90%
which is also valuable.

00:26:18.090 --> 00:26:21.270 align:middle line:84%
And get this, a
gratitude exercise

00:26:21.270 --> 00:26:22.770 align:middle line:84%
as part of your
spiritual practice

00:26:22.770 --> 00:26:25.260 align:middle line:84%
can boost mitochondrial
enzymes that

00:26:25.260 --> 00:26:29.100 align:middle line:84%
make you happier, more positive,
and more emotionally open.

00:26:29.100 --> 00:26:32.320 align:middle line:84%
And it takes two weeks of
gratitude practice to do that.

00:26:32.320 --> 00:26:35.220 align:middle line:84%
And with that, you
have my gratitude

00:26:35.220 --> 00:26:38.310 align:middle line:84%
for spending the last
half hour with me.

